The President and First Lady extend their greetings and best wishes to Muslims worldwide for a happy Eid-ul-Adha and safe travels to those performing Hajj. They acknowledge the millions of pilgrims from over 160 countries, including the United States, who have gathered in Mecca to perform the Hajj rituals and stand together in prayer. The President also highlights the significance of Eid-ul-Adha, which commemorates Abraham's willingness to sacrifice his son and emphasizes the shared values and common roots of three major religions. On behalf of the American people, they wish everyone a blessed Hajj season and Eid Mubarak.